<div id="review_2805828126" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2805828126" />
    <a title="Hayden" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/83119879-hayden"><img alt="Hayden" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1608441416p2/83119879.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2805828126?book_show_action=true">May 26, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Hayden" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Hayden" href="/user/show/83119879-hayden">Hayden</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/83119879-hayden?shelf=loved">loved</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2805828126" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7392720480031074905">Before I read the first of Mick Miley&apos;s series of autobiographies, I skipped to the second book &apos;Foley is Good: And the Real World is Faker than Wrestling&apos; which instantly became one of my all-time favourites. Although I can say with some guilt that I prefer its sequel, &apos;Have a Nice Day&apos; still stands as a magnificent original.<br/>Showcasing Foley&apos;s life and career from his home video days as Dude Love to his classic matches in WWF, the author throws in his brutal honesty, witty humour and relatable </span>
  <span id="freeText7392720480031074905" style="display:none">Before I read the first of Mick Miley's series of autobiographies, I skipped to the second book 'Foley is Good: And the Real World is Faker than Wrestling' which instantly became one of my all-time favourites. Although I can say with some guilt that I prefer its sequel, 'Have a Nice Day' still stands as a magnificent original.<br />Showcasing Foley's life and career from his home video days as Dude Love to his classic matches in WWF, the author throws in his brutal honesty, witty humour and relatable struggles into the mix as he presents to us a land filled with not-so-generous WCW bosses, harsh ECW fanbases, explosive (literally) Japanese death matches, and creative fireworks in his turn towards becoming a staple in the legendary Attitude Era. Foley describes the wrestling world and its characters with humble and honest detail as to show it as a business and its wrestlers as human beings, and his description of brutal matches leave you with goosebumps.<br />Although different from its sequel that focuses on the politics and controversies of WWF at its time, this brilliant autobiography shows us the story of a man who stands no chance of being a top star putting his body on the line to have that one chance to prove everyone wrong. In every word, we see that Foley is a wrestling legend, a fantastic writer and one hell of a person!</span>
  <a data-text-id="7392720480031074905" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


