<div id="review_1979389835" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1979389835" />
    <a title="Sophie Crane" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/67016485-sophie-crane"><img alt="Sophie Crane" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1577390926p2/67016485.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1979389835?book_show_action=true">Apr 28, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sophie Crane" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sophie Crane" href="/user/show/67016485-sophie-crane">Sophie Crane</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/67016485-sophie-crane?shelf=sports">sports</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/67016485-sophie-crane?shelf=wwe">wwe</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1979389835" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1531702612251072879">Mick Foley is one of those wrestlers that I enjoyed watching, but wouldn’t describe as a favourite. The book was cheap so I thought I’d give it a shot.<br/>It’s a massive book, and I’m only about a third of the way through, but I wanted to write this while I remember.<br/>The writing style is easy to read and as a result you sort of just go with the flow and find yourself reading way more than you maybe planned. There’s a certain humour to the writing that makes you happy the book is so thick.<br/>When reading</span>
  <span id="freeText1531702612251072879" style="display:none">Mick Foley is one of those wrestlers that I enjoyed watching, but wouldn’t describe as a favourite. The book was cheap so I thought I’d give it a shot.<br />It’s a massive book, and I’m only about a third of the way through, but I wanted to write this while I remember.<br />The writing style is easy to read and as a result you sort of just go with the flow and find yourself reading way more than you maybe planned. There’s a certain humour to the writing that makes you happy the book is so thick.<br />When reading autobiographies, I tend to get most interested when I’m reading about a time frame I knew about - eg I watched Mankind in the WWF (as it was at the time), so I expected not to find his earlier work as interesting. I was wrong. His easy, seemingly honest writing got me hooked from the start and I find myself genuinely interested about his experiences before he got into WWE.<br />While I can’t recall exact examples (I’m not finding them, the book is massive) I do remember at least a couple parts where I thought he was being petty or he just didn’t come across as very likeable in that instance. That is, however the honesty I mentioned. He tells you everything from his point of view, and wether you think he was right or wrong is up to you to decide.<br />This book is written well, has some interesting stories and reads almost like someone is talking to you, rather than you reading it, it has that kind of easy flow and pull you in and keep you style.<br />This book has elevated Foley to one of my favourite wrestlers, so if you were already a fan you will definitely love this book!</span>
  <a data-text-id="1531702612251072879" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


