              <span id="reviewTextContainer1958570307" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6363454147266527501"><b>Rating - 8.3</b><br/><br/>Enough insider information to keep me happy but the impressive part is the dedication/determination that are required if you even want to have a sniff of success; Kudos to Foley for creating a genre<br/><br/>Spawns questions on whether the ephemeral periods of money, power and sex are worth the pain that is endured when it is all gone; Appreciate Mick&apos;s real triple h&apos;s - humour, honesty and humility <br/><br/><br/></span>
  <span id="freeText6363454147266527501" style="display:none"><b>Rating - 8.3</b><br /><br />Enough insider information to keep me happy but the impressive part is the dedication/determination that are required if you even want to have a sniff of success; Kudos to Foley for creating a genre<br /><br />Spawns questions on whether the ephemeral periods of money, power and sex are worth the pain that is endured when it is all gone; Appreciate Mick's real triple h's - humour, honesty and humility <br /><br /><br /></span>
