<div id="review_2499313445" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2499313445" />
    <a title="Stacey Bryan" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/27528741-stacey-bryan"><img alt="Stacey Bryan" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1389320075p2/27528741.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2499313445?book_show_action=true">Aug 22, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Stacey Bryan" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Stacey Bryan" href="/user/show/27528741-stacey-bryan">Stacey Bryan</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2499313445" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8037825991894811296">I loved this book. I read it quickly and it was very entertaining. You do need to be at least a small amount of a wrestling fan to really enjoy it and I have been for many years. A small wrestling fan. I could tell you v little about the sport right now. This did make me rethink my love of WCW. And Ric Flair. The only reason I didn’t give this book 4 stars is bc of the blatant homophobia. There is a lot of it in there. Even for the late 90s when it was published, it’s a lot. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


